---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Pagination from '../../../components/Pagination.astro';
const base = '/portfolio';
const previous = 'expression-evaluator';
const next = 'huffman-compression';
---
<BaseLayout title="Elevator | ADEN Project" base={base}>
  <Pagination base={base} section="projects/aden" previous={previous} next={next} />
  <h1>Elevator Control System</h1>

  <section style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <p>
      Embedded control project modeling elevators, scheduling, and finite state machines. Focus areas were sensor integration, state transitions, and measuring user-facing metrics such as wait time.
    </p>
    <img src={`${base}/images/sprocket-shaft-drawing.png`} alt="Elevator diagram placeholder" style="width:100%; max-width:720px; border-radius:12px; border:1px solid #ddd; margin-top:1rem;" />
  </section>

  <section id="phases" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <h2>Project Phases</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Requirements and sensor selection: define floor detection and safety requirements.</li>
      <li>Control design: finite state machine for elevator motion and call assignment logic.</li>
      <li>Implementation: motor control, sensor debouncing, and timing logic.</li>
      <li>Testing & analysis: metrics collection, performance tuning, and reflection.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section id="design" style="margin-bottom:1rem; padding:1rem; border:1px solid #ddd; border-radius:10px; background:#fff8f0;">
    <h2>Design Notes</h2>
    <p>
      Design artifacts and notes are included in the reflections linked below; these contain wiring sketches, state diagrams, and the decision rationale for safety and timing choices.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="analysis" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <h2>Summary of Analysis</h2>
    <p>
      Analysis focused on responsiveness versus stability tradeoffs: more aggressive timing reduced wait times but increased overshoot. The chosen configuration balanced smoothness and responsiveness for the simulated environment.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="reflections" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <h2>Key Learnings & Reflections</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Finite state machines make control logic explicit and testable.</li>
      <li>Real-time timing (SysTick) and debouncing are critical for reliable sensors.</li>
      <li>Documenting design decisions speeds up debugging and peer review.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <strong>Reflections:</strong>
      <a href={`${base}/documents/reflections/html/${encodeURIComponent('Elevator Reflection 1.html')}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">#1</a>
      {' '}|{' '}
      <a href={`${base}/documents/reflections/html/${encodeURIComponent('Elevator Weekly Reflection 2.html')}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">#2</a>
      {' '}|{' '}
      <a href={`${base}/documents/reflections/html/${encodeURIComponent('Elevator Weekly Reflection 3.html')}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">#3</a>
      {' '}|{' '}
      <a href={`${base}/documents/reflections/html/${encodeURIComponent('Elevator Weekly Reflection 4.html')}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">#4</a>
    </p>
    <p><a href={`${base}/aden-course`} style="color:#0055aa; text-decoration:underline;">← Back to ADEN Course</a></p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>